cards.name: Adaptive Automaton
cards.text:
As Adaptive Automaton enters the battlefield, choose a creature type.
Adaptive Automaton is the chosen type in addition to its other types.
Other creatures you control of the chosen type get +1/+1.

cards.name: Aetherflux Reservoir
cards.text:
Whenever you cast a spell, you gain 1 life for each spell you've cast this turn.
Pay 50 life: Aetherflux Reservoir deals 50 damage to any target.
cards.flavor: While most power is used for ordinary, everyday tasks, one shouldn't underestimate its potential for the extraordinary.

cards.name: Altar of Dementia
cards.text: Sacrifice a creature: Target player mills cards equal to the sacrificed creature's power.
cards.flavor:
"It is not that you will go mad. It is that you will beg for madness."
-Volrath

cards.name: Ashnod's Altar
cards.text: Sacrifice a creature: Add {C}{C}.
cards.flavor:
"If you work at sawing up carcasses, you notice how the joints fit, how the nerves are arrayed, and how the skin peels back."
-Ashnod, to Tawnos

cards.name: Astral Cornucopia
cards.text:
Astral Cornucopia enters the battlefield with X charge counters on it.
{T}: Choose a color. Add one mana of that color for each charge counter on Astral Cornucopia.

cards.name: Blackblade Reforged
cards.text:
Equipped creature gets +1/+1 for each land you control.
Equip legendary creature {3}
Equip {7}
cards.flavor: It spilled the blood of one elder dragon. In Gideon's hands, it may yet taste another's.

cards.name: Bone Saw
cards.text:
Equipped creature gets +1/+0.
Equip {1} ({1}: Attach to target creature you control. Equip only as a sorcery.)
cards.flavor: In a world where death is always violent, cruel weapons are as common as rocks.

cards.name: Burnished Hart
cards.text: {3}, Sacrifice Burnished Hart: Search your library for up to two basic land cards, put them onto the battlefield tapped, then shuffle.
cards.flavor: Forged by divine hands to wander mortal realms.

cards.name: Caged Sun
cards.text:
As Caged Sun enters the battlefield, choose a color.
Creatures you control of the chosen color get +1/+1.
Whenever a land's ability causes you to add one or more mana of the chosen color, add one additional mana of that color.

cards.name: Chromatic Lantern
cards.text:
Lands you control have "{T}: Add one mana of any color."
{T}: Add one mana of any color.
cards.flavor: By guild tradition, any puddle of multicolored light on the cobblestones can serve as neutral ground.

cards.name: Chromatic Star
cards.text:
{1}, {T}, Sacrifice Chromatic Star: Add one mana of any color.
When Chromatic Star is put into a graveyard from the battlefield, draw a card.

cards.name: Cloud Key
cards.text:
As Cloud Key enters the battlefield, choose artifact, creature, enchantment, instant, or sorcery.
Spells you cast of the chosen type cost {1} less to cast.
cards.flavor: The musical sound of its turning triggers the tumblers of revelation.

cards.name: Defense Grid
cards.text: Each spell costs {3} more to cast except during its controller's turn.
cards.flavor: It lights up the sky, beckoning enemies only to repel them.

cards.name: Door to Nothingness
cards.text:
Door to Nothingness enters the battlefield tapped.
{W}{W}{U}{U}{B}{B}{R}{R}{G}{G}, {T}, Sacrifice Door to Nothingness: Target player loses the game.
cards.flavor: Only a madman could create such a door. Only an imbecile would open it.

cards.name: Elsewhere Flask
cards.text:
When Elsewhere Flask enters the battlefield, draw a card.
Sacrifice Elsewhere Flask: Choose a basic land type. Each land you control becomes that type until end of turn.
cards.flavor: One night Oona bottled the sky. The next night she aligned the stars and released it.

cards.name: Foundry Inspector
cards.text: Artifact spells you cast cost {1} less to cast.
cards.flavor: Automaton inspectors ensure that the Consulate's stringent standards for mass production are upheld.

cards.name: Gilded Lotus
cards.text: {T}: Add three mana of any one color.
cards.flavor:
"The perfection of the lotus reminds me of my hopes for this world . . . and my failures. I will not rest until I've atoned for them."
-Karn

cards.name: Goblin Charbelcher
cards.text: {3}, {T}: Reveal cards from the top of your library until you reveal a land card. Goblin Charbelcher deals damage equal to the number of nonland cards revealed this way to any target. If the revealed land card was a Mountain, Goblin Charbelcher deals double that damage instead. Put the revealed cards on the bottom of your library in any order.

cards.name: Helm of the Host
cards.text:
At the beginning of combat on your turn, create a token that's a copy of equipped creature, except the token isn't legendary. That token gains haste.
Equip {5}

cards.name: Howling Mine
cards.text: At the beginning of each player's draw step, if Howling Mine is untapped, that player draws an additional card.
cards.flavor: The mine's riches never end, nor do the moans of the spirits doomed to haunt them.

cards.name: Ichor Wellspring
cards.text: When Ichor Wellspring enters the battlefield or is put into a graveyard from the battlefield, draw a card.
cards.flavor:
"Our glorious infection has taken hold."
-Elesh Norn, Grand Cenobite

cards.name: Inspiring Statuary
cards.text: Nonartifact spells you cast have improvise. (Your artifacts can help cast those spells. Each artifact you tap after you're done activating mana abilities pays for {1}.)
cards.flavor: Ghirapur's most celebrated inventors have been immortalized in clockwork.

cards.name: Ivory Tower
cards.text: At the beginning of your upkeep, you gain X life, where X is the number of cards in your hand minus 4.
cards.flavor: Valuing scholarship above all else, the inhabitants of the Ivory Tower reward those who sacrifice power for knowledge.

cards.name: Jalum Tome
cards.text: {2}, {T}: Draw a card, then discard a card.
cards.flavor: Most books simply deliver knowledge. This one expects some in return.

cards.name: Journeyer's Kite
cards.text: {3}, {T}: Search your library for a basic land card, reveal it, put it into your hand, then shuffle.
cards.flavor:
"From the clouds, you can see as far as the distant horizon. It's a reminder of the infinite possibilities of everyday life."
-Noboru, master kitemaker

cards.name: Keening Stone
cards.text: {5}, {T}: Target player mills X cards, where X is the number of cards in that player's graveyard.
cards.flavor: As it spins, dead voices shriek in an ever-increasing cacophony, rending the mind asunder.

cards.name: Key to the City
cards.text:
{T}, Discard a card: Up to one target creature can't be blocked this turn.
Whenever Key to the City becomes untapped, you may pay {2}. If you do, draw a card.
cards.flavor: It would be unfortunate if the key fell into the wrong hands.

cards.name: Liquimetal Coating
cards.text: {T}: Target permanent becomes an artifact in addition to its other types until end of turn.
cards.flavor:
"They'll soon become accustomed to wearing skin that is not their own."
-Elesh Norn, Grand Cenobite

cards.name: Lodestone Golem
cards.text: Nonartifact spells cost {1} more to cast.
cards.flavor:
"Somehow it warps the Æther. It brings a strange weight, a blockade in the flow of spellcraft."
-Noyan Dar, Tazeem lullmage

cards.name: Mazemind Tome
cards.text:
{T}, Put a page counter on Mazemind Tome: Scry 1.
{2}, {T}, Put a page counter on Mazemind Tome: Draw a card.
When there are four or more page counters on Mazemind Tome, exile it. If you do, you gain 4 life.

cards.name: Mesmeric Orb
cards.text: Whenever a permanent becomes untapped, that permanent's controller mills a card.
cards.flavor: A step in one direction is two steps away from another.

cards.name: Millstone
cards.text: {2}, {T}: Target player mills two cards.
cards.flavor: Minds, like mountains, are never so grand and mighty that they can't be reduced to dust.

cards.name: Mind's Eye
cards.text: Whenever an opponent draws a card, you may pay {1}. If you do, draw a card.
cards.flavor: "Ideas drift like petals on the wind. I have only to lift my face to the breeze."

cards.name: Mishra's Bauble
cards.text: {T}, Sacrifice Mishra's Bauble: Look at the top card of target player's library. Draw a card at the beginning of the next turn's upkeep.
cards.flavor:
"Arcum is a babbling fool! Phyrexian technology is our greatest blessing. Take this delightful trinket for instance . . ."
-Heidar, Rimewind master

cards.name: Mox Amber
cards.text: {T}: Add one mana of any color among legendary creatures and planeswalkers you control.
cards.flavor: A moment in time made tangible, it has the power to realize epic visions.

cards.name: Mystic Forge
cards.text:
You may look at the top card of your library any time.
You may cast artifact spells and colorless spells from the top of your library.
{T}, Pay 1 life: Exile the top card of your library.

cards.name: Ornithopter
cards.text: Flying
cards.flavor: Once a year, the skies over Paliano fill with the flying machines of this who hope to be taken as pupils by the artificer Muzzio.

cards.name: Perilous Vault
cards.text: {5}, {T}, Exile Perilous Vault: Exile all nonland permanents.
cards.flavor: The spirit dragon Ugin arranged the hedrons of Zendikar to direct leylines of energy. To disrupt one is to unleash devastation and chaos.

cards.name: Phyrexian Processor
cards.text:
As Phyrexian Processor enters the battlefield, pay any amount of life.
{4}, {T}: Create an X/X black Phyrexian Minion creature token, where X is the life paid as Phyrexian Processor entered the battlefield.

cards.name: Platinum Angel
cards.text:
Flying
You can't lose the game and your opponents can't win the game.
cards.flavor: She is the apex of the artificer's craft, the spirit of the divine called out of base metal.

cards.name: Precursor Golem
cards.text:
When Precursor Golem enters the battlefield, create two 3/3 colorless Golem artifact creature tokens.
Whenever a player casts an instant or sorcery spell that targets only a single Golem, that player copies that spell for each other Golem that spell could target. Each copy targets a different one of those Golems.

cards.name: Pristine Talisman
cards.text: {T}: Add {C}. You gain 1 life.
cards.flavor:
"Tools and artisans can be destroyed, but the act of creation is inviolate."
-Elspeth Tirel

cards.name: Psychosis Crawler
cards.text:
Psychosis Crawler's power and toughness are each equal to the number of cards in your hand.
Whenever you draw a card, each opponent loses 1 life.
cards.flavor:
"If that brain can't figure out the secret of the serum, then add more brains."
-Rhmir, Hand of the Augur

cards.name: Quicksilver Amulet
cards.text: {4}, {T}: You may put a creature card from your hand onto the battlefield.
cards.flavor: Those who examine the amulet too closely have been known to become part of its ornate carvings.

cards.name: Quietus Spike
